 Python OOP Assignment
Assignment 1: Design Your Own Class

In this task, i created a Smartphone class that demonstrates key OOP concepts.

Inheritance â†’ Smartphone inherits from Device.

Encapsulation â†’ The storage attribute is private (__storage).

Constructors â†’ Objects are initialized with unique values.

Methods â†’ Actions like charge() and get_storage().

 Code Example
# Parent class
class Device:
    def __init__(self, brand, model):
        self.brand = brand
        self.model = model

    def info(self):
        return f"{self.brand} {self.model}"

# Child class (Inheritance + Encapsulation)
class Smartphone(Device):
    def __init__(self, brand, model, storage, battery):
        super().__init__(brand, model)   # inherit brand & model
        self.__storage = storage        # private attribute (Encapsulation)
        self.battery = battery

    def charge(self, amount):
        self.battery += amount
        print(f"ğŸ”‹ Battery charged to {self.battery}%")

    def get_storage(self):
        return f"ğŸ“± Storage: {self.__storage}GB"

# Create unique objects
phone1 = Smartphone("Samsung", "Galaxy S25", 256, 80)
phone2 = Smartphone("Apple", "iPhone 16", 512, 50)

print(phone1.info())        # Samsung Galaxy S25
print(phone1.get_storage()) # ğŸ“± Storage: 256GB
phone1.charge(10)           # ğŸ”‹ Battery charged to 90%

 Activity 2: Polymorphism Challenge

In this task, i created different vehicle classes that share the same method name (move()), but each defines its behavior differently.

 Code Example
class Vehicle:
    def move(self):
        print("This vehicle moves ğŸš™")

class Car(Vehicle):
    def move(self):
        print("ğŸš— Driving on the road")

class Plane(Vehicle):
    def move(self):
        print("âœˆï¸ Flying in the sky")

class Boat(Vehicle):
    def move(self):
        print("ğŸš¤ Sailing on water")

# Polymorphism in action
vehicles = [Car(), Plane(), Boat()]

for v in vehicles:
    v.move()
  OUTCOMES
1 Driving on the road
2 Flying in the sky
3 Sailing on water

